'''Club Nacional de Regatas El Mbiguá''' (most commonly known as ''"Club Mbiguá"'') is a [[Sports club|multisport]] club based in [[Asunción]], [[Paraguay]]. The club was founded on May 6, 1902 as a [[Rowing (sport)|rowing]] club.<ref>[http://www.nacionalquerido.com/Historia.htm GÉNESIS FUNDACIONAL] - Nacional Querido Website {{Es icon}}</ref>

The club is famous in Paraguay for its rowing team and takes advantage of its location along the banks of the [[Paraguay River]] to train its athletes. The club also has a [[field hockey]] team and had a brief stint in [[football (soccer)]] when it participated in the [[Primera División de Paraguay|Paraguayan first division]] tournament in 1909 and 1910.<ref>[http://rsssf.com/tablesp/parahist.html#09 Paraguay - League History 1906-1964] by Karel Stokkermans at [[RSSSF]]</ref>

