{{Infobox football club |name = KF Vëllaznimi |image =| |image_size = 200px |fullname = Klubi i Futbollit Vëllaznimi Gjakovë |nickname = ''Kuq e Zinjët'' (Red & Blacks) |founded = {{Start date and age|1927}} |ground = [[City Stadium (Gjakova)]] |capacity = 6.000 |chairman = [[Agim Cana]] |manager = Gani Sejdiu |league = [[First Football League of Kosovo]] |season = [[First Football League of Kosovo|2018–2019]] |position = 9th (relegated) |points = |website = www.vellaznimi.com |pattern_la1=_black_stripes|pattern_b1=_blackstripes|pattern_ra1=_black_stripes |leftarm1=ff0000|body1=ff0000|rightarm1=ff0000|shorts1=000000|socks1=000000 |pattern_la2=|pattern_b2=|pattern_ra2= |leftarm2=9CE0FF|body2=9CE0FF|rightarm2=9CE0FF|shorts2=ffffff|socks2=9CE0FF }}
'''FC Vëllaznimi''' (Klubi i Futbollit Vëllaznimi) is a [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Gjakova]], in western [[Kosovo]]{{ref label|status|a|}}. The club was founded in 1927 and currently plays in the first division of football in Kosovo, the [[Football Superleague of Kosovo]].
==History== [[File:TrepcaVëllaznimi.jpg|thumb|[[KF Trepça]] vs KF Vëllaznimi on 5 June 2008.]] KF Vëllaznimi are nine-time champions of Kosovo and together with [[FC Prishtina]] they are one of the most successful football clubs in Kosovo. The club had its golden years during the 1960s, '70s and '80s when it dominated the Kosovo Province League. The club played in Serbian league system until the Kosovo War in 1999. It was known in its Serbo-Croatian form, as '''FK Vlaznimi Đakovica'''.
