{{Infobox gymnast | name = Marta Linares | gender = w | image = File:Marta Linares.PNG | image_size = 150px | caption = | fullname = Marta Linares García | altname = | nickname = | country = {{flagu|Spain}} | regions = | formercountry = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1986|1|31|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Castellón de la Plana]], Spain | hometown = | residence = | death_date = | death_place = | height = 5-7.5 (172 cm) | weight = 106 lbs (48 kg) | discipline = RG | level = Senior International Elite | natlteam = 2001 — 2006 | club = Club Deportivo Lledó | gym = | collegeteam = | headcoach = | assistcoach = | formercoach = | choreographer = | music = | eponymousskills = | retired = | worldranking = | updated = | show-medals = yes | medaltemplates = <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] --> }}
'''Marta Linares García''' (born 31 January 1986 in [[Castellón de la Plana]]) is a Spanish group [[rhythmic gymnast]] representing her nation at international competitions.
She participated at the [[2004 Summer Olympics]], in the [[Gymnastics at the 2004 Summer Olympics – Women's rhythmic group all-around|group all-around event]],<ref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/li/marta-linares-1.html}}</ref> together with [[Sonia Abejón]], [[Bárbara González]], [[Isabel Pagán]], [[Carolina Rodríguez]] and [[Nuria Velasco]] finishing 7th in the final after finishing 8th in the qualification. She competed at world championships, including at the [[2005 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships]].<ref>{{cite web |title=2005 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships athletes – Marta Linares |url=http://gym.longinestiming.com/File/000004010100FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF01 |publisher=Longinestiming.com |date= |accessdate=27 January 2016}}</ref>
