{{Infobox non-profit | name              = Panathlon Foundation | image             = | type              = Sports [[Charitable organization|Charity]] | founded_date      = <!--{{Start date|df=yes|1996|MM|DD}}--> | tax_id            = | registration_id   =1072638 | founder           = Ashley Iceton | location          = [[England]] | coordinates       = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LON|display=inline,title}} --> | origins           = | key_people        = | area_served       = | product           = | mission           = | focus             = | method            = | revenue           = | endowment         = | num_volunteers    = | num_employees     = | num_members       = | subsid            = | opponents         = | owner             = | non-profit_slogan = | former name       = | homepage          = {{URL|http://www.panathlon.com}} | dissolved         = | footnotes         = }}

The '''Panathlon Foundation''' is a sports charity that enables children with disabilities in England to have competitive sporting opportunities.<ref name="crozier">{{cite web|url=http://www.theleisurereview.co.uk/articles09/panathlon.html |title=Take your partners for the Panathlon |date=April 2009 |accessdate= |author=Crozier, Katie |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101102045006/http://www.theleisurereview.co.uk/articles09/panathlon.html |archivedate=2 November 2010 }}</ref><ref name="hubbard">{{cite web|url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/9063/alan-hubbard-on-why-he-is-pleased-the-panathlon-is-bouncing-back|title=Alan Hubbard: On why he is pleased the Panathlon is bouncing back|date=23 February 2010|accessdate=19 May 2012|author=Hubbard, Alan}}</ref>

Formed in 1996 by Ashley Iceton,<ref name=hubbard/> the Panathlon Foundation Ltd (registered charity 1072638),<ref>{{cite web | url=http://opencharities.org/charities/1072638 | title=The Panathlon Foundation limited | accessdate=19 May 2012}}</ref> provides sports coaching within schools, sports equipment to schools, sports training to teachers, coaches and young leaders, and sports competitions.<ref name="independent">{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/general/others/inside-lines-the-nice-girl-who-has-an-entire-nation-whooshing-on-a-star-1905835.html |title=Inside Lines: The (n)ice girl who has an entire nation whooshing on a star - "A Bonus for Bojo" |date=21 February 2010 |agency=The Independent |accessdate=19 May 2012 |author=Hubbard, Alan |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100224023036/http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/general/others/inside-lines-the-nice-girl-who-has-an-entire-nation-whooshing-on-a-star-1905835.html |archivedate=24 February 2010 }}</ref> Panathlon is aimed at children aged 5 to 19 years with [[Physical disabilities]] and [[Learning Disabilities]].<ref name="football">{{cite web|url=http://www.footballfoundation.org.uk/news/archive/pre-2012-press-releases/?EntryId15=21953 |title=Major investment by Football Foundation in disability sport and the Panathlon Challenge |publisher=The Football Foundation |accessdate=19 May 2012 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160524142010/http://www.footballfoundation.org.uk/news/archive/pre-2012-press-releases/?EntryId15=21953 |archivedate=24 May 2016 }}</ref> They also have a specific visual impairment and deaf program.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|url=http://ukdeafsport.org.uk/the-panathlon-challenge/ |title=UK Deaf Sport - The Panathlon Challenge |date= |access-date= }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> Panathlon works with SEN schools and SEN units in mainstream schools currently across 27 counties in England in 2015.<ref name="crozier" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.efds.co.uk/news/4456_record-breaking_participation_numbers_for_panathlon |title=EDFS, Record-breaking participation numbers for Panathlon |date= |access-date= }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>

Panathlon has 6 sports programs: Multi-Sport, Primary Panathlon, Swimming, Football, Impairment Specific, Boccia. The Multi-Sports competition involves the disability specific sports of [[Table Cricket]], Polybat, New Age Kurling, [[Boccia]] and adapted Athletics. Football includes U13 and U16 5-a-side football & Girls Only Football. Impairment specific involves Powerchair Athlete Days, Visual Impairment & Deaf coaching & competitions. Boccia includes a partnership with Boccia England to deliver the Lord's Taverners Boccia competitions.<ref name=independent/><ref name=football/><ref name=":3" /><ref name="school">{{cite web|url=http://www.yourschoolgames.com/uploads/file/inter_format_Panathon-web.pdf |title=Panathlon in School Games Initiative |accessdate=19 May 2012 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304031919/http://www.yourschoolgames.com/uploads/file/inter_format_Panathon-web.pdf |archivedate=4 March 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.london2012.com/blog/2009/04/an-electric-atmosphere-at-a-sports-competition-for-young-people-with-disabil.php |title=An electric atmosphere at a sports competition for young people with disabilities |date=2 April 2009 |accessdate=19 May 2012 |author=Robert |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101231221417/http://www.london2012.com/blog/2009/04/an-electric-atmosphere-at-a-sports-competition-for-young-people-with-disabil.php |archivedate=31 December 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=|title=You Tube, "Panathlon deliver Lord Taverner's Boccia"|date=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g9v1efluThg|accessdate=2016-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.greenbanksportsacademy.co.uk/panathlon-challenge-deaf-football-tournament/ |title=Greenbank Sports Academy, "Panathlon Challenge Deaf Football Tournament" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525135343/http://www.greenbanksportsacademy.co.uk/panathlon-challenge-deaf-football-tournament/ |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref>

In the 2009 academic year Panathlon’s work involved 2,500 children in 5 counties in England.<ref name="hubbard" /><ref name="school" /><ref name="jack">{{cite web|url=http://www.jackpetcheyfoundation.org.uk/panathlon |title=The Jack Petchey Foundation "Panathlon Challenge" |accessdate=19 May 2012 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306054716/http://www.jackpetcheyfoundation.org.uk/panathlon |archivedate=6 March 2016 }}</ref> By 2015 academic year Panathlon's work involved 7,500 children from 27 counties in England.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newsshopper.co.uk/news/bromley/14328861.PICTURED__Disabled_south_east_London_students_take_on_Panathlon_Challenge/?ref=rss |title=News Shopper "Disabled students from Bexley, Bromley, Lewisham and Greenwich compete in Panathlon Challenge" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160524154829/http://www.newsshopper.co.uk/news/bromley/14328861.PICTURED__Disabled_south_east_London_students_take_on_Panathlon_Challenge/?ref=rss |archivedate=24 May 2016 }}</ref>

The charity has six patron, ex-Paralympian's [[Danny Crates]],<ref name="danny">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_xntY6w4qsU|title=You Tube, Interview, "Panathlon Challenge Sky Sports Highlights with Danny Crates Introducing"|accessdate=19 May 2012}}</ref> [[Liz Johnson (swimmer)|Liz Johnson]],<ref>{{Citation|last=|title=You Tube, Interview, "Panathlon Liz Johnson in Kent"|date=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E2nmhvCeIk8&context=C38331c1ADOEgsToPDskKR5_uGBQ8tCk8IOCtHkiZn|accessdate=2016-05-24}}</ref> [[Helen Turner]],<ref>{{Citation|last=|title=You Tube, "Panathlon Helen Turner in Kent"|date=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jNGtEQ5vjOI&context=C38331c1ADOEgsToPDskKR5_uGBQ8tCk8IOCtHkiZn|accessdate=2016-05-24}}</ref> [[Steve Brown (wheelchair rugby)|Steve Brown]],<ref>{{Citation|last= |title=Steve Brown Patron of the Panathlon Challenge |date= |url=http://posabilitymagazine.co.uk/steve-brown-patron-of-the-panathlon-challenge/ |accessdate=2016-05-24 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160524152832/http://posabilitymagazine.co.uk/steve-brown-patron-of-the-panathlon-challenge/ |archivedate=24 May 2016 }}</ref> current Paralympian Louise Sugden <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.northlondon-today.co.uk/article.cfm?id=109083&headline=Youngsters%20do%20the%20borough%20proud%20in%20Panathlon%20Challenge&sectionIs=sport&searchyear=2016 |title=North London Press, "Youngsters do the borough proud in Panathlon Challenge" |last=Dominique Stafford in Youth Sport |date=March 2016 |access-date=2016-05-24 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160524152547/http://www.northlondon-today.co.uk/article.cfm?id=109083&headline=Youngsters%20do%20the%20borough%20proud%20in%20Panathlon%20Challenge&sectionIs=sport&searchyear=2016 |archivedate=24 May 2016 }}</ref> and TV presenter [[Alex Brooker]].<ref>{{Citation|last=|title=You Tube, Interview "Panathlon Challenge Introduction to Alex Brooker"|date=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XkgkTCQ7Ab8|accessdate=2016-05-24}}</ref> Guests at Panathlon competitions include former sports minister [[Kate Hoey]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hhQbhPQJGGA&context=C38331c1ADOEgsToPDskKR5_uGBQ8tCk8IOCtHkiZn|title=YouTube, Interview, "Kate-Hoey-Panathlon"|accessdate=19 May 2012}}</ref> ex-Paralympian and TV Presenter [[Giles Long]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=np1JuzbbsiU&context=C38331c1ADOEgsToPDskKR5_uGBQ8tCk8IOCtHkiZn|title=YouTube, Interview, "GilesLong-Panathlon"|accessdate=19 May 2012}}</ref> and a host of Paralympian's, Adam Alderman,<ref>{{Citation|last=|title=You Tube, Interview, "Panathlon Adam Alderman in Essex"|date=2011-05-20|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ac4FfhRzE70&context=C38331c1ADOEgsToPDskKR5_uGBQ8tCk8IOCtHkiZn|accessdate=2016-05-24}}</ref> Freya Levy,<ref>{{Citation|last=|title=You Tube, Interview "Freya Levy on Panathlon"|date=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VdzP1P4knQI|accessdate=}}</ref> [[Graham Edmunds]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.emmahollowayfoundation.co.uk/ |title=Emma Holloway Foundation, "Helping youth disability sport in Suffolk" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525103721/http://www.emmahollowayfoundation.co.uk/ |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref> Ben Lampert,<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.eastlondonlines.co.uk/2014/03/hackney-kids-win-wembley-football-tournament/ |title=East London Lines, "Hackney kids win Wembley football tournament" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150531134921/http://www.eastlondonlines.co.uk/2014/03/hackney-kids-win-wembley-football-tournament/ |archivedate=31 May 2015 }}</ref> Josh Beacham,<ref name=":0" /> Tim Prendegast,<ref>{{Citation|last=|title=You Tube, Interview, "Tim Prendegast at Primary Panathlon"|date=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kblVpFMDq_w|accessdate=}}</ref> Dervis Konuralp,<ref>{{Citation|last=|title=You Tube, Interview, "Dervi