n 2014"|date=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cyRH_4ePJ7I|accessdate=2016-05-24}}</ref> Steve Brown replaced Jody Cundy in the London Triathlon 2015 Panathlon Team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newhamrecorder.co.uk/news/triathletes_take_on_royal_docks_course_1_4187820 |title=Newham Recorder "Triathletes take on Royal Docks course" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150910081001/http://www.newhamrecorder.co.uk/news/triathletes_take_on_royal_docks_course_1_4187820 |archivedate=10 September 2015 }}</ref> Hilton Hotel Stansted hosting virtual 'Around the World in a Day' events.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.essex.police.uk/news_features/features_archive/2010/november_2010/around_the_world_in_a_day.aspx |title=Around the world in a day |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525123557/https://www.essex.police.uk/news_features/features_archive/2010/november_2010/around_the_world_in_a_day.aspx |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.saffronwaldenreporter.co.uk/news/hilton_london_stansted_raise_record_amount_for_essex_sport_disability_charity_1_716468?usurv=skip |title=Saffron Walden Reporter, "Hilton London Stansted raise record amount for Essex sport disability charity" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525123848/http://www.saffronwaldenreporter.co.uk/news/hilton_london_stansted_raise_record_amount_for_essex_sport_disability_charity_1_716468?usurv=skip |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref>

Media Appearances: Panathlon London final was featured on [[Sky Sports]] in June 2010.<ref name="danny" /> Panathlon Central London Final was featured on BBC1 Breakfast Saturday in April 2013.<ref>{{Citation|last=|title=You Tube, "Panathlon on BBC1 Breakfast Report"|date=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ql-5DGyb1MU|accessdate=}}</ref> East England regional final was featured on ITV East Anglia in October 2014.<ref>{{Citation|last=|title=You Tube, "ITV East Anglia Panathlon East Regional Final 23rd October 2014"|date=|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Olr_VFsX5OU|accessdate=}}</ref>

Panathlon have been involved at the Queen Elizabeth II Olympic Park. 20 Panathlon Athletes from the 5 Olympic London Boroughs raced on the 100 metre track at the [[London Olympic Stadium]] Gold Challenge test event in April 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1010168/panathlon-challenge-youngsters-beat-usain-by-four-months |title=Panathlon Challenge youngsters beat Usain to Olympic Stadium finish line |date=3 April 2012 |publisher=Insideworldparasport |accessdate=19 May 2012 |author=Gold, David |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160524145907/http://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1010168/panathlon-challenge-youngsters-beat-usain-by-four-months |archivedate=24 May 2016 }}
</ref> From 2014 the London Finals Multi-Sports competition has been at The Copper Box Arena.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1016898/copper-box-arena-to-host-panathlon-london-final |title=Copper Box Arena to host Panathlon London Final |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525111426/http://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1016898/copper-box-arena-to-host-panathlon-london-final |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref> From 2015 Panathlon's South England Swimming Finals have been hosted by The Olympic Pool.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gazette-news.co.uk/news/13377854.Children_compete_in_mini_Paralympics_style_swimming_competition_at_Olympic_Park/ |title=Daily Gazette Essex County Standard, "Teams from Market Field and Doucecroft Schools" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525111916/http://www.gazette-news.co.uk/news/13377854.Children_compete_in_mini_Paralympics_style_swimming_competition_at_Olympic_Park/ |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref> John Lewis Stratford, onlooking the park, have hosted the Panathlon Jack Petchey Outstanding Achievement Award Ceremony since 2012. This awards ceremony contains three prizes: Individual Achievement, Sports Achievement & Outstanding Sports Leader Achievement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wandsworthguardian.co.uk/news/10102671.Medal_winning_Mahfuz_is__an_inspiration_/?ref=arc |title=Wandsworth Guardian, "Medal-winning Mahfuz is an inspiration" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525111203/http://www.wandsworthguardian.co.uk/news/10102671.Medal_winning_Mahfuz_is__an_inspiration_/?ref=arc |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.efds.co.uk/news/4712_dagenham_student_crowned_panathlon_champion_2015 |title=EDFS, "Dagenham student crowned Panathlon Champion 2015" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525102238/http://www.efds.co.uk/news/4712_dagenham_student_crowned_panathlon_champion_2015 |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://posabilitymagazine.co.uk/inspirational-ilford-teenage-crowned-panathlon-champion/ |title=PosAbility Magazine, "Inspirational Ilford teenage crowned Panathlon champion" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141207042056/http://posabilitymagazine.co.uk/inspirational-ilford-teenage-crowned-panathlon-champion/ |archivedate=7 December 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.efds.co.uk/news/2031_panathlon_challenge_celebrate_outstanding_achievement_awards_2013|title=EDFS, "Panathlon Challenge celebrate Outstanding Achievement Awards 2013"|website=|access-date=}}</ref>

Panathlon have another annual Celebration of Individual Talent, their Wembley Stadium Trust Primary Awards.<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wnst.org.uk/panathlon-award-2016/ |title=Wembley National Stadium Trust, "Panathlon Award 2016" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525112943/http://www.wnst.org.uk/panathlon-award-2016/ |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ablemagazine.co.uk/sophie-named-outstanding-achiever-at-primary-panathlon/ |title=Able Magazine, "Sophie named outstanding achiever at Primary Panathlon" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318060956/http://ablemagazine.co.uk/sophie-named-outstanding-achiever-at-primary-panathlon/ |archivedate=18 March 2016 }}</ref>

Other notable venues that have hosted Panathlon competitions are Stoke Mandeville Stadium,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.leamingtoncourier.co.uk/sport/campion-and-myton-schools-team-up-for-panathlon-success-1-6754832 |title=Leamington Courier, "Campion & Myton Schools team up for Panathlon success" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525121846/http://www.leamingtoncourier.co.uk/sport/campion-and-myton-schools-team-up-for-panathlon-success-1-6754832 |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref> The NIA Birmingham (Barclaycard Arena), Wembley Stadium Powerleague <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/news/local-news/powerleague-pitches-wembley-stadium-hosted-6775512 |title=Get West London, "Powerleague Pitches at Wembley Stadium hosted Panathlon tournament" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525114106/http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/news/local-news/powerleague-pitches-wembley-stadium-hosted-6775512 |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref>

In February 2016 Panathlon celebrated its 20th Anniversary at City Hall with Kate Hoey and five Paralypian's in attendance.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.efds.co.uk/news/4959_hoey_hails_panathlon |title=EDFS, "Hoey hails Panathlon" |date= |access-date= |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160525105546/http://www.efds.co.uk/news/4959_hoey_hails_panathlon |archivedate=25 May 2016 }}</ref>

