'''Union Sportive de la Médina d'El Harrach''' ({{lang-ar|الإتحاد الرياضي لمدينة الحراش}}), known as '''USM El Harrach''' or simply '''USMH''' for short, is an [[Algeria]]n [[Association football|football]] club based in [[El Harrach]], [[Algiers]]. The club was founded in 1935 as '''Union Sportive Musulmane Maison-Carréenne''' and its colours are yellow and black. Their home stadium, [[Stade 1er Novembre 1954 (Algiers)|Stade 1er Novembre 1954]], has a capacity of 5,000 spectators. The club is currently playing in the [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 2]].

USM El Harrach has won three national titles, the [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1|Algerian Championnat National]] in 1998 and 2 [[Algerian Cup]]s in 1974 and 1987.

